Good length ball on off, Abbas defends it out onto the pitch.
That's nasty from Jamieson but Abbas plays it well. Short ball around off, Abbas sways away from it.
Short ball around middle, Abbas ducks under it.
Good length ball on off, Ashraf solidly blocks it out.
Fullish ball outside off, Ashraf pushes it to cover.
Short ball down the leg side, Faheem leaves it alone.

FOUR! Falls in open spaces! Southee goes backwards but it goes over. Short ball around middle, Ashraf pulls it towards deep square leg. Southee, who was standing a little ahead of the fence, tries going back but the ball goes over for a boundary.
Bouncer around middle, Ashraf ducks under it.
Gets hit on the body! Short ball around leg, Ashraf lets it hit him on the arm.
Back of a length ball on middle, Abbas blocks it to mid on.
Shortish ball outside off, Abbas shoulders arms to it.
Full ball on off, Abbas solidly defends it towards mid off.
Mohammad Abbas is in at 9.

OUT! CAUGHT! New Zealand are on fire in the last few overs! Yasir Shah walks off in disappointment. Kyle Jamieson is elated and New Zealand are just three wickets away from a victory.  The last few overs have been good for the Kiwis. Jamieson runs in and bowls a short one around off, Yasir Shah has a poke at it. It takes the outside edge and goes towards gully where Tim Southee takes the catch. Pakistan have 19.4 overs to survive in the day.
Full ball on off, Shah defends it to mid off.
Short ball on middle, Shah ducks under it.

MISFIELD AND FOUR! Full and around off, Faheem strokes it down the ground. Boult runs to his right in anticipation to stop the ball but it lands on one of the footmarks and bounces away from his diving effort. 20 overs remaining in the day.
Good length and around off, blocked.
Down the leg side. Faheem looks to flick but misses.
Another short ball but this time Faheem opts to sit under it.
Short again and Faheem pulls again. This time he finds the fielder at square leg.
FOUR! Faheem is not going to just block. A short ball from Wagner and Faheem swivels and hammers it down to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Full on off, Shah is solid in defense.
Full ball on middle, Yasir defends it back to the bowler.
Short ball on middle, Ashraf pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
On middle, solidly defended out.
Back of a length ball on off, Ashraf camps on his back foot and then defends it to the off side.
Short ball around middle, Ashraf ducks under it.
Yasir Shah comes out to bat.

OUT! TAKEN DOWN THE LEG SIDE! Wagner is the man who gets the big wicket. Massive, massive wicket. Wagner bangs it short again and this one is down the leg side. With all the close-in fielders in the sight, Fawad looks to slams it down the leg side. He goes for the pull but ends up gloving it behind. Watling gobbles the chance to his right. The marathon knock from Fawad is over. Can term it as a soft dismissal but you got to give it to Wagner. The Kiwi workhorse just kept banging it short. Alam resisted and resisted, almost entire Day 5. But this time around, he went for the shot, maybe to push the fielders back but he pays the price. He walks off with standing ovation from the crowd. A gritty knock comes to an end and New Zealand are in with a big chance now. 22 overs left in the day for them to remove the remaining 4.
Short ball around middle, Alam ducks under it.
Back of a length ball on middle, Alam blocks it out.
Wagner comes around the wicket and bowls a good length ball on middle, Fawad defends it back to the bowler.
Full toss on middle, Alam is shocked as he looks to defend. It hits the upper part of the bat and rolls onto the pitch.
Full ball on middle, Alam defends it back to the bowler.
Faheem is off the mark! Back of a length ball outside off, Ashraf punches it through the gully region and picks up a couple before the fielder cuts it off.
Full ball on off, Ashraf defends it out onto the pitch.

An appeal for LBW turned down! Probably going over the stumps! Short ball around middle and off, Faheem looks to pull but misses and gets hit on the pads. Jamieson appeals but nothing from the umpire. Southee from behind signals that it is high.
Short ball around middle, Ashraf sits under it.
Good length ball on off, Faheem solidly defends it to cover-point.
Fullish on middle, Ashraf pushes it down to mid on.
Good length ball on middle, Fawad is solid in defense.
Full ball on middle, Alam plays it back to the bowler.
On a length on the pads, Alam looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad.
On off, Alam bunts this towards cover.
Good length ball on off, Alam defends it to the off side and says no for the single.
Full ball on middle, Alam defends it out onto the pitch.
Short ball around middle, Ashraf ducks under it.
Faheem Ashraf walks in next, replacing skipper Rizwan. What an innings it was from him in the first inning. He needs to do something similar here.

OUT! LBW! All reds it is and Mohammad Rizwan has to go! End of a wonderful knock from the skipper. New Zealand desperately needed that wicket and they will feel that they have an opening in this game. Can they win this from here? Jamieson bowls a good length ball on middle, Rizwan looks to flick but misses and gets rapped on the pads. New Zealand put up a huge shout for LBW but nothing from the umpire. The Kiwis take the review. The Ultra Edge shows no bat while the Ball Tracker shows all reds. The Kiwis are ecstatic. Pakistan need 133 in 25.1 overs.

Review time! Has Jamieson got his man here? The umpire thinks otherwise but Williamson has reviewed it. Big moment in the game. Let's see what the replays have got to show. Ultra Edge first. No bat. Time for the Ball Tracker. Three Reds. Rizwan has to go. What a review from New Zealand.
Very full delivery on the pads, Alam flicks it to fine leg and picks up a single.
Short ball outside off, Alam punches it to the off side.
On middle, Alam defends it out.
Fullish ball on middle, Alam pushes it to mid on.
Good length ball outside off, Rizwan shoulders arms to it.  26 overs to go in the game. Pakistan need 134 runs.
Outside off, Rizwan leaves it alone.
Slower ball outside off, Rizwan leaves it alone.
On a length on off, Rizwan punches it to mid off.
Full ball outside off, Rizwan drives it to mid off for a dot.
EDGY! Full ball outside off, Rizwan looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Good length ball on middle, Alam works it to mid-wicket.
Another bumper around middle, Alam ducks under it.
Short ball around middle, Alam ducks under it.
Full ball on middle and leg, Alam flicks it to mid-wicket for a dot.
On a length on off, Fawad blocks it to cover.
Full ball on off, keeping a little low. Alam does well to get his bat down in time and defend it out.
Just short! Fullish ball outside off, Rizwan drives it uppishly. Luckily for Rizwan, it lands safely in front of the cover fielder.
On middle, nudged to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on off, MR pushes it to mid off.
Back of a length ball on off, solidly defended onto the pitch.
Full ball on off, Rizwan drives it to mid off.
Fullish ball on off, Rizwan shuffles across and then defends it to point.
Back of a length ball on middle, Alam goes on his back foot and then defends it out.
Fullish ball on off, solidly defended out.
On a length on middle, Alam tucks it to mid-wicket.
Short ball around middle, Alam ducks under it.
Short ball on middle, Rizwan pulls it to deep square leg for a run.
Full ball on middle, Rizwan works it to mid-wicket.
Bowling change! Kyle Jamieson is back on. 17-9-29-0 from him so far.
Good length ball on middle, Alam lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball on off, Alam defends it to the off side.
NO BALL! Another one! Good length ball outside off, Alam leaves it alone.
On off, defended.
Good length and around off, a solid block from him. Wagner oversteps.
Watches the next one outside off all the way to the keeper as he shoulders arms.
Good length and around off, solidly defended.

FOUR! CENTURY FOR FAWAD! What a knock! What a player. He has proven his worth here. He was ignored for a number of years, in spite of performing consistently in the domestic arena.  Made a comeback eventually against England earlier in the year but got out without scoring in the first innings upon his return. Didn't do much in the next game either but here he is. Got a chance and has bailed his team out of trouble with a superb century. His second in Tests. The first one came nearly 12 years ago, in his debut game. What a moment. Something to savor for him and every Pakistan fan. Gets to the landmark by slamming this short ball wide of the man at deep mid-wicket. The fielder there ran to his left and dived to stop but missed it. Take a bow, Fawad Alam. Looks at the heavens and celebrates. An emotional moment for him.
A solid front foot defense on the last ball of the over!
Lovely delivery from Boult but well defended too. A fuller ball around off, Rizwan pushes it to mid on.
Shortish and around off, poked towards the off side.
FOUR! Slammed! Short and wide outside off, Rizwan drags it from there and slams the pull wide of the man at deep square leg. Santner tries to get around but fails to do so.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
A single! Full and around middle, flicked to fine leg for one.
Good length ball around off, kept out.
Length ball around off, pushed towards point for nothing.
Very full and around off, Rizwan pushes it to mid off.
Banged short, Fawad pulls and takes a single to move to 96. He is a boundary away from his ton.
Good length and around middle again, Fawad defends it back to the bowler.
Good length and around middle and leg, worked to mid-wicket.
Landed around off, kept out solidly by Rizwan.
Good length and around off, pushed towards gully.
Good stop! Short and wide outside off, Rizwan punches it well but Nicholls dives to his right and makes a fine stop.
Fuller again, pushed to mid off.
Fuller and around off, a solid defense offered by Rizwan.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Down the leg side, tucked to fine leg for one. Rizwan will keep the strike for the next over.
Too short again to trouble Rizwan as he ducks.
Good length and around off, pushed towards point.
Bouncer around off this time. Once again Rizwan ducks.
This one is banged short and on middle, Rizwan sits under it.
FOUR! Runs flowing for Pakistan in this session. Short and wide outside off, Rizwan slashes it over backward point for a boundary. The 150-run stand is up between the two.
Neil Wagner will bowl from the other end. 17-4-27-0 are his numbers so far.
Landed around off on a length, Alam defends it out.
Good length and around off, kept out.

FIFTY FOR The SKIPPER! A fuller one around middle, he flicks it to deep square leg to get to the little milestone. Rizwan will know that the job is only half done. But he has led from the front here. Did something similar in the first innings and has done the same again.
Good length and around off, Rizwan strokes it to the right of the bowler and Boult gets a hand to it.
FOUR! Runs for Rizwan too! A boundary it is and he moves to 49. Overpitched and outside off, Rizwan leans forward and creams the drive through covers. No one is stopping that.
Run straightaway! Fuller and around off, Fawad flicks it wide of the of the man at mid on for one.

We are all in readiness to begin the final session of the first Test match between New Zealand and Pakistan. The New Zealand players make their way out to the middle, followed by Mohammad Rizwan and Fawad Alam. Trent Boult will start with the ball.
... Day 5, Session 3 ...

Right then! Pakistan have one session to survive while the hosts need 6 wickets. Will Pakistan manage to hold onto a draw or will New Zealand be able to take the remaining 6 wickets? Join us at around 1600 local (0300 GMT) for the final session of the game to find out what happens.

New Zealand bowlers have toiled hard but have not been able to break this partnership. They have tried all their bowlers but nothing seems to be going right for them at the moment. Santner was too short while Southee and Boult bowled well with the second new ball but they have not been rewarded. They have not been helped with the injury to Wagner who seems to lacking in pace. They will hope that they can take the remaining six wickets as soon as possible.

Mohammad Rizwan and Fawad Alam were simply superb. They have played just excellently and have hardly looked troubled at the crease. Fawad Alam has to be credited. He is just 6 short of a century and has looked assured at the crease while the skipper has also played extremely well and has hardly looked troubled at the crease.  They would look to do more of the same once the last session begins. They have a real chance of a draw and would come out hard in the last session.

A very good session for Pakistan! They have not lost a wicket in this session and Mohammad Rizwan and Fawad Alam are doing a wonderful job for their country. They are in the middle of a wonderful partnership and the Pakistan management will be very pleased with the efforts.
Flatter and around off, tucked to mid-wicket for nothing. With that, it is TEA ON DAY 5.
Loopy around off, Rizwan comes on the front foot to block.
FOUR! Rizwan pounces on this short ball. This is on middle, he rocks back and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tossd up and outside off, turns away as Rizwan watches it go to the keeper.
Short and wide outside off, Rizwan goes hard to cut but mistimes it towards point.
Huge appeal but turned down. Flat and around middle and leg, Rizwan looks to defense but misses to get hit on the pad. They appeal but it is turned down. Looked to be going down leg.
Mitchell Santner to bowl the last over before Tea.
Length around off, Alam defends this towards covers.
FOUR BYES! That took off from nowhere! Watling has no chance! Short around middle, Alam looks to pull but misses. Watling, behind the stumps, jumps but fails to collect it.
Length around middle, played towards covers by Alam.
Shortish around middle, Rizwan pulls this towards deep square leg for a run.
Shortish length around off, Rizwan leaves it alone.
Short and wide, Rizwan pulls this straight to mid on.
Length around off, Alam blocks this out.
Shortish around off, tucked towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries! Super shot! A fuller ball around middle, Fawad nails the drive through mid on for a boundary. Moves to 94 now.
FOUR! Lovely! Short and wide outside off, Alam stands tall and guides this past the gully fielder for a boundary.
Fuller around middle, flicked wide of mid on for a single.
Fuller ball around off, driven back to the bowler.
Fuller and around off, a solid front foot defense.

Bandged short and on middle, Alam pulls it wide of the man at deep square leg. Jamieson there runs to his right and does really well to get down and stop the ball near the fence. They check if it is a clean stop and it is. Two taken.
Around off on a length, kept out.
WIDE! What happened there? Everybody is having a laugh out there. Southee runs and bowls a full toss way outside off, Watling collects. Wided.
Almost gone! A length ball outside off, bounces and seams away a little away from the batsman.
Shortish around off, Alam bunts this down on the off side.
Fuller angling into the pads, Rizwan flicks it wide of mid on and takes a single.
Shortish and just around off, jumps off the surface as Rizwan looks to defend. The ball hits the upper part and it goes through gully for a run.

NOT OUT! It has bounced before going to the keeper! The joy from New Zealand was short-lived. Jamieson runs in and bowls a very full ball outside off, Rizwan looks to drive but it takes the bottom edge and goes to Taylor at first slip. He takes it and New Zealand think that they they have got their man. Chris Gaffaney was going to give it out but then says wait a minute and wants to have a look upstairs. The soft signal is not out. The replays roll in and the it shows that it has bounced after hitting the bat. Not out will be signal.

Has that gone straight into the hands of the fielder or has it bounced? The soft signal is not out.  It looks close. The front foot is fine. Multiple angles roll in and it shows that it has bounced in front after hitting the bat.
There is a slight halt in play as something has gone in Rizwan's eye and the physio is coming out to have a look at him.
FOUR! Lovely drive. Simply superb! Fullish outside off, Rizwan leans into the drive and creams this one through the covers for a boundary.
Fuller this time around off, Alam leans on the drive towards mid on and they take three before the fielder returns it back. That was just a mere push but had good timing on that did Alam.
Short of a length outside off, Alam bunts this on the off side.
Length ball outside off, Alam blocks this out.
Kyle Jamieson is back on.
Length outside off, Alam guides this past gully to collect a run.
Good length outside off, Alam leaves that alone.
Fuller length outside off, Alam looks to defend but it goes off the inner half of the bat towards mid on.
Full ball outside off, Alam pushes it to cover.
Back of length ball outside off, Alam leaves it alone.
Back of a length ball on middle, Rizwan nudges it to deep square leg for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! What a shot from Alam! Good length ball outside off, Alam stands tall and then punches it through the cover-point region for a boundary.
Fullish ball on off, Fawad pushes it to cover.
Short ball around off, Alam pulls it back towards the bowler.
Full ball outside off, Alam lets it go to the keeper.
Full ball on the pads, Alam works it to mid-wicket.
Length ball on middle, solidly defended back to the bowler.
Full ball outside off, Rizwan shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball on middle, defended out onto the pitch.
Nicely played! Good length ball on the pads, Rizwan flicks it through square leg and picks up a couple before the fielder cuts it off.
Back of a length ball on off, Rizwan blocks it to point.
Good length ball on middle, Rizwan works it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on off, Alam taps it to point.
Length ball on middle and leg, Alam flicks it to deep square leg for a couple.
EDGY FOUR! 100-run stand comes up in a streaky manner but Pakistan won't mind. Good length ball on off, Alam looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and it goes past gully for a boundary.
Full on middle, worked to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on middle, Alam defends it towards mid on.
Good length ball on the pads, Alam looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Good length ball outside off, Rizwan has no problems in leaving it alone.
Fullish ball on off, Rizwan defends it to cover.
BEATEN! That stays down! Good length ball around off, keeping a little low. Rizwan looks to defend but it sneaks under his bat and goes to Watling.
Outside off, left alone by Rizwan.
Good length ball outside off, Rizwan watches it carefully and then decides to leave it alone.
Good length ball on the pads, Alam flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Back of a length ball on off, Rizwan defends it to cover.
BEATEN! What a beauty from Boult! Just brilliant! Good length ball around off, Rizwan looks to block but beats the outside edge.
Fuller ball outside off, Rizwan leaves it alone.
Back of a length ball on off, Rizwan defends it to cover.
BEATEN! Lovely ball from Boult! Full ball outside off, moving away. Rizwan looks to defend but the ball whizzes past the outside edge and it goes to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Rizwan leaves it alone.
Trent Boult is into the attack. 15-4-43-2 are his numbers so far.
Full ball on off, Alam defends it to cover-point.
EDGY AGAIN! Southee bowls an in-swinger on off, Alam looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge towards gully.
EDGY! Rizwan is lucky there. Good length ball on off, Rizwan looks to defend but it takes the inside edge and it goes towards square leg for a single.
Fuller ball outside off, inviting Rizwan for the drive but Rizwan is not interested and leaves it alone.
Full ball outside off, moves away after pitching. Rizwan though shoulders arms to it.
Southee starts with a back of a length ball on middle, Rizwan defends it out onto the pitch.
The second new ball has been taken and it will be Tim Southee who will be making the first use of it. 15-7-21-2 are his figures so far.

Drinks! Pakistan are fighting and fighting hard. Both Mohammad Rizwan and Fawad Alam have played superbly so far and they look pretty comfortable at the crease. The visitors would want to carry on and continue the good work while the Kiwis would hope that they can break this stand quickly. The second new ball is available now and the hosts should take it immediately. Let's see what pans out.
Full on middle, Alam defends it out onto the pitch.
Floated on middle, Alam defends it out.
On middle, played towards mid on for a single.
Just wide of the fielder! Loopy ball on off, Rizwan looks to drive but it goes uppishly. Luckily for Rizwan, it is wide of the fielder at short cover.
Some turn there! Flatter on off, spinning in. Rizwan looks to cut at first but then adjusts and then pushes it to cover.
Tossed up outside off, Rizwan pushes it to cover.
Neil Wagner is limping off the field.
Very full on the pads, Alam works it down to mid on.
Well played and well controlled! Short ball around off, Rizwan pulls it with control towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Slower ball on off, Rizwan waits for it and then blocks it to cover.
Fullish ball on off, Rizwan defends it to silly mid off.
Back of a length ball on off, Rizwan goes back in his crease and defends it to the cover region.
Good length ball on off, Rizwan defends it to cover.
On middle, Alam defends it back to the bowler. A maiden over.
Floated ball on middle, Alam tucks it to mid on for nothing.
Tossed up on middle, Alam works it back to the bowler.
Shorter and outside off, Alam cuts it straight to point.
Quicker on off, pushed towards mid off.
Flatter ball outside off, Alam plays it to cover.
Ok! Here's skipper. With the second new ball 3 overs away, Kane brings himself on.
Fuller and around off and middle, driven to mid on for nothing by Rizwan.
Similar ball around off, Rizwan covers the stumps and blocks it.
Length ball around off, Rizwan defends it solidly.
Almost gets the edge! A length ball pitched around off, hits a crack and shapes away from the batsman. Rizwan goes for the drive but gets beaten comprehensively there.
Length around off, Alam hits it towards point and gets a single.
Length ball around off, defended back to the bowler.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Rizwan defends it onto the pitch.
A couple now! Santner once again bowls it short and this one is on off, Rizwan punches it through the covers for a couple.
Full on the pads, Rizwan once again plays it back to the bowler.
Drifter from Santner, Rizwan is solid in defense.
Loopy ball on middle, Rizwan prods forward and defends it back to the bowler.
Too short from Santner! He bowls it outside off, Alam goes on his back foot and then punches it to deep cover for a single.
Good length ball on off, Rizwan defends it back to the bowler.
Full ball on the pads, Alam works it to deep square leg for a single.
Short ball outside off, Fawad cuts but finds the gully fielder. Good effort from Nicholls there.
Full ball on off, Alam blocks it to the bowler.
Fullish ball on middle, Alam pushes it towards mid on.
Good length ball on middle, Alam defends it out.
Neil Wagner is into the attack.
Loopy ball outside off, Rizwan leaves it alone.
Shortish and outside off, Rizwan cuts it straight to point.
Quicker on middle, Rizwan defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off, Rizwan guides it to first slip.
Outside off, left alone by Rizwan.
Flatter outside off, Alam cuts it though point for a single.
Floated on the pads, Alam plays it to short leg. Santner has overstepped. No Ball given.

Almost chops it on his stumps! Fawad is lucky here. A short ball just outside off, Fawad looks to punch but gets an inside edge. The ball goes towards leg gully. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but he misses. It was a needless throw and there is no one to back it up. They run two more.
Slightly short around off, Alam cut its straight to point.
Length around off, pushed towards cover.
Length ball on middle, Alam blocks this out.
Length ball around middle, defended solidly by Alam.
Very full on middle, Alam pokes that towards point.
Quicker ball on middle, Rizwan prods forward and defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter on the pads, Rizwan looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad.
Flatter around off, played straight to covers by Rizwan.
Fuller around off, tucked towards covers.
Flatter around middle, defended solidly by Rizwan.
Flatter around off, poked towards point.
Length on off, Alam gets behind that and blocks it.
Length around off, blocked solidly by Alam.
Close! A fuller ball outside off, Fawad looks to fend but misses and the ball goes through to the keeper. An appeal is made by the keeper but nothing from the umpire.
Shortish around off, pushed in the gap at point for a brace.
Length ball on off, defended solidly.
On off, defended out.
Tossed up outside off, Rizwan pushes it to cover.
Short ball down the leg side, Rizwan looks to pull but misses. Watling whips the bails off but Rizwan was in.
Tossed up on middle, defended back to the bowler.
Flatter ball on the pads, Rizwan looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad.
EDGY! Floated ball on off, Alam looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and it goes past the first slip fielder for a single.
Flatter ball outside off, Rizwan punches it to cover-point for a single.
Back of a length ball on middle, tucked to square leg.
Good length ball on middle, Fawad blocks it back to the bowler.
On middle, this is worked to square leg for a single.

An appeal for LBW turned down! Good length ball the pads, Rizwan looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. Jamieson puts up an appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Rizwan seems to have injured himself but is fine to continue.
Back of a length ball on off, Rizwan is solid in defense.
Good length ball down the leg side, Rizwan looks to flick but misses.
PLAY AND A MISS! Good length ball outside off, Rizwan looks to cut but the ball goes to the keeper. Jamieson has overstepped. No Ball signalled.
FOUR! This is poor bowling from Santner! He bowls it short again on middle, Fawad camps on his back foot and then pulls it to deep square leg for a boundary. 150 up for Pakistan.
FOUR! Nicely played! Too short from Santner! He bowls it outside off, Alam cuts it through the cover-point region for a boundary.

An appeal for LBW turned down! Tossed up around off, Alam pads it away. Santner appeals but the umpire is not interested. The Kiwi players discuss among themselves whether to take the review but decide against it.
Tossed up outside off, Rizwan lunges forward and drives it to cover for another run.
Loopy ball on the pads, Alam flicks it uppishly but wide of the fielder for a single.
Full and outside off, Rizwan drives it wide of mid off for a single.
Good length ball on middle, Fawad tucks it to mid-wicket for a dot.
Good length ball outside off, Alam leaves it alone.
Fullish ball on middle and leg, Fawad tucks it to mid-wicket.
Almost chopped on! Brilliant delivery from Jamieson! Short ball around off, Alam looks to duck at first but the ball does not rise as enough. It takes the inside edge and goes past the stumps.
Back of a length ball on off, Alam taps it to gully off the back foot.
Short ball around middle, Alam ducks under it.
Who will bowl from the other end? It is Kyle Jamieson.
FIFTY! Excellent innings so far from Fawad Alam! This is a very important innings from the left-hander. Tossed up on middle, Fawad tucks it to deep square leg for a single.
Tossed up on middle, Rizwan flicks it to square leg for a single.
Tossed up on middle, Rizwan prods forward and defends it back to the bowler.
Quicker on off, Rizwan defends it out off the back foot.
BEATEN! That's what Santner is looking for. Loopy ball outside off, spinning away. Rizwan looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Santner starts with a flatter ball outside off, Alam punches it to deep cover for a single.

We are all in readiness to begin the post-Lunch session! The Kiwi players make their way out to the middle and they are followed by Mohammad Rizwan and Fawad Alam. Mitchell Santner will start with the ball.
... Day 5, Session 2 ...

Right! An engrossing first session is done and dusted! Two more left. The game is poised nicely now! Another similar session and Pakistan will be more confident about drawing the game. The Kiwis, on the other hand, will have to break this stand quickly in the next session to have a crack at the remaining batters. Join us for the second session at around 1340 local (0040 GMT) to find out how things pan out.

It was a tough morning session for the Kiwis. Boult struck early but they had to work really hard otherwise. They didn't give away any freebies to the Pakistan batters though and made sure scoring wasn't easy. Wagner deployed the short ball tactics but it didn't work for him as he didn't get any success with it as his pace dipped a little owing to his toes injury. Santner too bowled a few tight overs too but the wickets never came.

The day started poorly for Pakistan as they lost experienced Azhar Ali in the 2nd over of the session. However, Fawad Alam was ready to play the big knock as he kept blocking everything that was thrown at him. Wagner tested him with a barrage of short balls but nothing worked. Skipper Rizwan dug in as well along with him in this session. The duo have now added 62 so far and would look to continue doing so when they return for the 2nd session.

Just one wicket lost and Pakistan will be mighty pleased with their efforts as they take the honours of winning the session. Credit to Fawad and Rizwan for fighting it out in the middle. The Kiwis will not be too disappointed as there is still plenty of overs left in the day to get the remaining 6 wickets.

Let's see how things pan out in this remaining first session.

We are all set to begin the final day of this Test match. The New Zealand players are making their way out to the middle, followed by Azhar Ali and Fawad Alam. Tim Southee will start with the ball.

Azhar Ali is there for a chat. He says that 90 overs is a long time and it is not easy to bat in these conditions. Adds that they will look to play session by session. States that as an international player, he needs to put his hands up and do the job for the team. Tells that the pitch has gone a little slow and if they play themselves in, they can bat long.

Just 7 wickets needed for the Kiwis to win! They have dominated this game thus far and now they would hope that they show their best performance and get the remaining wickets quickly. Pakistan, on the other hand, would look to bat and bat and try to salvage a draw from this game. They need 302 runs more which is unlikely so a draw would be a viable option for them. Join us in a while.
... Day 5, Session 1 ...

Right then! On Day 5, Pakistan would hope that they can bat and bat and salvage a draw from this game. It looks difficult for them but they have to believe that they can achieve that and bat hard. The hosts, on the other hand, will want to break this stand first and then look to finish things quickly on Day 5. The last day of this Test will be played on 30th December 2020 at around 1100 local (2200 GMT, the previous day). Join us for that. Until then, cheers and take care.

Tim Southee is there for a chat. He says that he was very happy but there is still plenty of work to be done on Day 5. Adds that they tried to get as much off the surface with the hard ball and it was a terrific start. Goes onto say that they need to be switched on right from the start against a quality opposition. Adds that he loves Test cricket and he wants to play for as long as he can. States the example of James Anderson who is doing a wonderful job for England. Tells that he shares some great moments with the team and was happy to see the crowd cheering. Southee says that he loved watching Glenn McGrath and he learned a lot from Chris Martin and Shane Bond and they were massive parts in the early part of his career. States that Boult has bowled exceptionally well and a big performance from him is around the corner.

The visitors did not start off well with the bat. They lost both their openers for a duck before Haris Sohail fell soon after. But Azhar Ali and Fawad Alam have done well to see the day off. They batted cautiously and defended the ball solidly and put the bad ones away. They though would know that there is still a long way to go and they cannot afford to go complacent on Day 5. A lot will depend on this partnership if they want to save this game.

Now coming onto the bowling from New Zealand, Tim Southee was superb with the ball as he was swinging the ball both ways and kept on troubling the Pakistan batters. He was rewarded with two wickets and in the meanwhile, he brought up his 300th Test wicket. Trent Boult was brilliant as well while Jamieson was economical. The only worry for them might be the injury to Neil Wagner who was clearly in discomfort with his broken toe and his involvement for Day 5 is yet to be known. All-in-all, it was a great performance from the Kiwis.

The bowling from Pakistan was not bad but then they were behind the 8-ball since the start of the third innings and were always going to play catch-up. Shaheen Afridi bowled exceedingly well at the start but was unlucky that the few edges did not go to hand. The pick of the bowlers though was Naseem Shah who bowled with pace and was rewarded with three wickets.

The day started with New Zealand starting their second innings and they did that perfectly. Tom Latham and Tom Blundell started out cautiously but once they settled in, the runs flowed from their bat and they stitched a 100-plus stand before Blundell was castled. Tom Latham and Kane Williamson added a few quick runs before the hosts lost a few quick wickets in search of runs. They eventually declared with a lead of 372.

Fawad Alam and Azhar Ali have managed to survive Day 4 but it was New Zealand's day. They have dominated this Test so far and are on the verge of taking a 1-0 lead in the 2-match Test series on Day 5. Kane Williamson will be a very happy skipper.

Drinks! It is fair to say that New Zealand are keeping on dominating the game. They have been simply superb with the ball in hand and they have not given anything away. Tim Southee has been the pick of the bowlers as he reached 300 Test wickets while Boult and Jamieson too have bowled superbly. Pakistan, on the other hand, are in dire straits at the moment. Nobody, barring Azhar Ali, has looked so settled in the crease and they need to perform out of their skins to salvage anything from this game. What will happen in the final hour of the day's play? Trent Boult is back into the attack. 7-3-18-1 are his figures so far.

We are back for the final session of Day 4! The New Zealand players stride out to the middle, followed by Azhar Ali and Haris Sohail. Trent Boult will start with the ball for the final session of Day 4.
... Day 4, Session 3 ...

Right then! New Zealand would hope that they continue to do the good work that their bowlers have done so far and try to take the remaining wickets as quickly as possible. Pakistan, on the other hand, need something special if they want to save this game. Join us at 1600 local (0300 GMT) for the final session.

Trent Boult is down for an interview. He says that he is happy with the way New Zealand is performing in this test. Adds that he is looking to keep it tight. Mentions they need 8 wickets for the victory and they will look to win it easily.

Pakistan, on the other hand, have been poor. They bowled decently but New Zealand had done their work by then. They then needed to see off the Tea session without any hiccups but they failed to do so as they lost two in no time and are in serious pressure right now. They have a long way to go and they would want their batsmen to stick it out in the middle.

New Zealand came out to bat with intent. They batted positively with Latham and Blundell playing wonderful knocks. Some contributions from the middle order helped New Zealand take a lead of 372 which looks more than enough on this wicket. If that was not enough, the Kiwi bowlers came out all guns blazing. Boult and Southee were breathing fire and plucked out two wickets with 0 runs on the board. Kane Williamson could not have asked for a better start from their bowlers. They are well on top in this game.

What a session for New Zealand! They go into the break with their heads held high. 2 wickets in five overs! Just brilliant stuff from the hosts and they are well on their way to take a 1-0 lead in the Test series. Pakistan will be very disappointed with their effort.
